   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "narrative": "David Lee Owens, born June 18, 1947, was a Lance Corporal in the United States Marine Corps and the son of John and Frankie (Abrams) Owens. He was killed on October 5, 1966, at just 19 years old, at Quang Tri — the northernmost province of South Vietnam, hard against the Demilitarized Zone, where the Marines fought a grinding war against North Vietnamese regulars. He gave his life in one of the war's most dangerous corners, a Holyoke Marine barely out of boyhood. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
