   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "narrative": "Henry A. Quirk of Holyoke served five years in the regular army before the war, and entered the service again in October 1917, stationed at Camp Devens with a Machine Gun Battalion. He had already crossed the Atlantic three times before that — and twice the ship beneath him was torpedoed and sunk. A man who had twice gone into the water with a sinking ship boarded a third and went back. He was killed in action in France in the autumn of 1918. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
