   "branchLabel": "U.S. Army – World War I",
   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "narrative": "Jefferson M. Smith of Holyoke entered the service on April 5, 1918, and was stationed at Fort Slocum, New York, with the Supply Company of the 71st Field Artillery. The supply companies hauled the shells, the fodder, and the rations forward over shelled roads by mule and truck, and an artillery regiment could not fire a round without them. He went overseas in August 1918 and died in France in October of influenza — killed, like so many, by the pandemic that traveled with the armies and struck the crowded camps and troopships harder than any battlefield. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
