   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "narrative": "Joseph W. Smith entered the regular army in 1916 and went to the Mexican Border with a New York regiment as a Second Lieutenant. He won promotion to First Lieutenant, and in France he earned his captain's bars. He had formerly been a First Lieutenant in Company D, 2nd Massachusetts Regiment — Holyoke's own company. Captain Smith was killed in action in France on September 2, 1918, serving with the 105th Infantry. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
