   "lat": null,
   "lng": null,
   "narrative": "Dr. Wilfred G. Drouin returned from France in March 1917 after eighteen months of active service in the Edith Cavell hospital in Paris. He had enlisted with the French Medical Corps and worked for weeks in underground hospitals near the front — at Bar-le-Duc near Verdun, and in the Somme region — and was at Verdun when Fort Vaux was captured. After receiving his commission from the United States Government on June 12, 1918, he was ordered to report to Camp Yaphank, Long Island. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
