   "narrative": "Henry E. McElwain, Jr., entered the Coast Artillery Corps at Chicago in July 1917 and was stationed at Camp Sheridan, then transferred to the Fortress Monroe Training School, where he received his commission as first lieutenant. He went overseas in May 1918 with Battery F, 60th Coast Artillery Corps; through that summer he served as acting regimental assistant adjutant and was sent to the headquarters of a French army to study its information service. He was commissioned a captain in October 1918. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
