   "narrative": "Wallace A. Choquette enlisted in Company D, 2nd Massachusetts Regiment, on June 29, 1910, rising through corporal and sergeant to be elected first lieutenant in 1913. He went to the Mexican border with Company D, serving a month as acting battalion adjutant and two and a half months in charge of No. 7 Truck Train. He went to France with Company D, 104th Infantry, was detached to attend an officers' training school in the French front-line trenches, and was assigned to the Tank Corps in June 1918. If you have further information about this veteran, please contact the City of Holyoke Veterans Graves Officer at (413) 322-5630 at 310 Appleton Street, 1st Floor, Holyoke, MA 01040.",
